title: Independent candidate Iftikhar Ali Mishwani wins PK-60 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Iftikhar Ali Mishwani has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-60, Mardan-VII by securing 29,186 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was ANP candidate Sher Afghan Khan who bagged 15,203 votes.
Voters turn-out remained 44.97 per cent.
